\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 Abram and Abram believed God, even against all odds. Abram knew the odds, and he had anticipated the dangers that lay ahead of him as he laid hold of the promises of God (the promised land). No person lays claim to a land that is occupied by others without facing opposition. Struggle after struggle was to confront Abram. But note: he had prepared ahead of time. He had joined hands with others, made a covenant\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 a treaty\hich\f1 \emdash \loch\f1 for mutual protection. The treaty was with the Amorite, Mamre, and his two brothers, Eshcol and Aner. Note that the valley where Abram and Mamre were living was named after Mamre.}
\par\plain {\f1\fs24\b0\i0\cf3 Thought 1. What a lesson for all believers! As we journey through life laying hold of the promises of God, we are confronted with struggle after struggle. Our only hope is to join hands with other believers for mutual protection. But we must prepare ahead, developing Christian fellowship and ministry. Then when the struggles come, we will know others who can stand with us, know them well enough that we can call upon them. This takes preparation, preparation ahead o"}
